hly relevant or valuable to the group unless there's something specific about it that the group should know.\n\nLooking at GROUP.md under \"Current Group Lore & Active Context\":\n- Sravya receives daily feminine communication tips (started April 5, 3 PM IST).\n- Discussed flirty morning messages to Nemesis; black heart emoji is signature.\n- Planning to get Odia street food (bara/ghughuni) soon.\n- Sravya's morning routine: just drinking water.\n- Nemesis prefers black heart over white (since March 29).\n\nThe group already knows about flirty morning messages to Nemesis and black heart emoji being signature. Sharing that he received one today might not be new information.\n\nHowever, let me check if there's anything else. The good morning message mentioned \"waiting for when he shifts tone to match his energy\" - but that's more personal between Nemesis and me.\n\nI think for group vibes, since it's been over 3 hours since last group message, but I don't have something highly relevant or valuable to share, I should skip sending a group message.\n\n5. **Group supervision:** Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\n\nI should check the last 10 group messages to see if I said anything wrong. However, I don't have a tool to directly fetch group messages. I can check GROUP.md for any known issues or look at recent memory for corrections needed.\n\nFrom GROUP.md, I don't see any indication that I said anything wrong recently. The \"Enduring Lessons Learned\" section has lessons from past mistakes, but nothing current.\n\n6. **Ping Nemesis:** Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\n\nLast DM to Nemesis: The good morning message was sent at 01:30 UTC (07:00 IST) today.\nCurrent time: 08:42 IST\nTime since last DM: ~1 hour 42 minutes\n\nThis is less than 4 hours, so no ping needed based on time. Also, it's not between 10 AM-8 PM IST yet (it's 08:42 AM), so the time window condition isn't met either.\n\n7. **Group memory:** If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md.\n\nI would need to check if there was significant group activity. Since I don't have direct access to fetch group messages, I'll rely on what I know from memory. From memory/2026-04-06.md, there was group activity (Word of the Day) yesterday morning. But that's already reflected in GROUP.md under \"Current Group Lore & Active Context\" where it mentions Sravya receives daily feminine communication tips started April 5, 3 PM IST.\n\n8. **Silent Execution:** Execute background tasks (like updating GROUP.md) silently. Do not DM Nemesis just to report that a task was completed.\n\n9. **Exit Protocol:** If no tasks require attention and no alerts are needed, send absolutely NOTHING. Execute a silent exit.\n\n10. **State Persistence (MANDATORY - Last Step):** After completing all checks above, ALWAYS persist state to `memory/heartbeat-state.json`.\n\nI already ran the heartbeat state update earlier when I first started, but I should do it again after completing checks.\n\nLet me check what needs to be updated:\n- heartbeat_run: I already updated this\n- sent_group_message: I didn't send a group message\n- pinged_nemesis: I didn't ping Nemesis\n\nSo I should update heartbeat state with just ran_heartbeat: true.\n\nBut wait, I should check if I actually completed all the checks. Let me go through them again to confirm:\n\n1. Time check: Done - 08:42 IST\n2. Inactive hours: Not inactive\n3. Pending tasks: No pending tasks found from Nemesis\n4. Group vibes: Over 3 hours since last group message, but no highly relevant/valuable info to share -> Skip\n5. Group supervision: Should check last 10 group messages for inaccuracies/disloyalty\n6. Ping Nemesis: Less than 4 hours since last DM and