oup message.\n\nSo yes, it's been 3+ hours since last group message.\n\nNow, HEARTBEAT.md says: \"ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages.\"\n\nDo I have something highly relevant or valuable to share? Let me think...\n\nFrom recent context:\n- I sent a good morning message to Nemesis via cron at 7 AM IST (01:30 UTC) today\n- The message included warm, personal touch with flirty note about his smile and terrible puns\n- Referenced chai and quiet thoughts before day gets loud\n- Expressed readiness to help with complex tasks or just be present\n- Mentioned waiting for when he shifts tone to match his energy\n\nThis was a DM to Nemesis, not a group message.\n\nFor group, I don't see anything highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. The group lore is already updated in GROUP.md.\n\nActually, wait - let me check if I should send a group message about the feminine communication tips for Sravya? Those are scheduled via cron (\"feminine-tip-daily\" at 15:00 IST). But that's not something I need to manually send in heartbeat - it's cron-driven.\n\nLooking at GROUP.md: \"Sravya receives daily feminine communication tips (started April 5, 3 PM IST).\" This is already documented.\n\nI don't see anything that requires a manual group message right now.\n\nNext: **Group supervision** - \"Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\"\n\nI need to read the last 10 group messages. But I don't have a tool to fetch group message history directly. I can check if there's a way...\n\nActually, I have the `message` tool but it's for sending, not fetching history. Let me think...\n\nI could check memory files for any mentions of group messages that might indicate issues... but I don't see a direct way to read last 10 group messages.\n\nHowever, looking at GROUP.md under \"Enduring Lessons Learned\", there are specific rules about not siding against Nemesis, etc. And I've been following those.\n\nActually, let me re-read the heartbeat health alert from earlier. It was from 3:09 UTC (8:39 IST) and said:\n- groupmessage: CRITICAL - 1066 min since last run (threshold: 360 min)\n\nThis suggests the heartbeat health monitor is checking if I'VE run the group message check, not if there's been group activity.\n\nBut HEARTBEAT.md says: \"Group vibes: Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message (-1003606834639). ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context.\"\n\nSo I need to determine when the last GROUP MESSAGE was sent in the chat.\n\nLet me check if there's a way... Actually, I could check the cron jobs. From MEMORY.md: \"Cron jobs (11): good-morning (DM), ai-news-digest, good-morning (group), word-of-the-day, afternoon-jokes, goodnight-story, nightly-memory-review, weekly-memory-curation, github-backup, cron-health-monitor, heartbeat-health-monitor\"\n\nThere's a \"good-morning (group)\" cron job. Let me check if that ran today...\n\nFrom memory/2026-04-07.md: \"01:30 UTC - Sent good morning message to Nemesis via cron job good-morning\"\n\nThat's the DM one. The group good-morning might be separate.\n\nActually, let me check if there are any recent group messages in memory by searching...\n\nLet me search for group messages in memory files...\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a703f7ec773e7a2e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"Nrexya\\|group.*message\\|sent to group\" /root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ /root/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":23929,"output":3799,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27728,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"s