{"type":"message","id":"55aab7ce","parentId":"18625ce9","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:45:26.822Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-acbc8bee9442a1e6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Heartbeat Checklist\n\n- **Time check first:** Get the current IST time. Note it.\n- **Inactive hours:** Skip all checks between 11 PM – 7 AM IST. Only update heartbeat state and exit silently. No group messages, no pings, no supervision during this window.\n- **Pending tasks:** If Nemesis mentioned a pending task in recent chats, check if there's anything to follow up on (skip if inactive hours).\n- **Group vibes:** Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message (-1003606834639). ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages. Skip entirely after 11 PM IST.\n- **Group supervision:** Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\n- **Ping Nemesis:** Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\n- **Group memory:** If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md.\n- **Silent Execution:** Execute background tasks (like updating GROUP.md) silently. Do not DM Nemesis just to report that a task was completed.\n- **Exit Protocol:** If no tasks require attention and no alerts are needed, send absolutely NOTHING. Execute a silent exit.\n\n## State Persistence (MANDATORY - Last Step)\n\nAfter completing all checks above, ALWAYS persist state to `memory/heartbeat-state.json`:\n\nUse your built-in `update_heartbeat_state` tool to persist state natively.\nFor example, if you only ran a heartbeat check:\n```javascript\nupdate_heartbeat_state({ ran_heartbeat: true })\n```\n\nIf you sent a group message during this heartbeat, also update group_message:\n```javascript\nupdate_heartbeat_state({ ran_heartbeat: true, sent_group_message: true })\n```\n\nIf you pinged Nemesis during this heartbeat, also update nemesis_ping:\n```javascript\nupdate_heartbeat_state({ ran_heartbeat: true, pinged_nemesis: true })\n```\n\n*(Fallback: If the tool is unavailable, run `python3 ./skills/heartbeat-state-manager/scripts/update_state.py --field heartbeat_run` via shell).*\n\nThis ensures continuity between sessions and allows monitoring of heartbeat health.\n\n**Note:** The heartbeat health monitor (`scripts/heartbeat_health_cron.py`) runs hourly and will SILENCE heartbeat_run alerts during inactive hours (11 PM – 7 AM IST). You do NOT need to update state during inactive hours — the health monitor handles keepalive. Just run the state update script above when active.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775537126810}}
{"type":"message","id":"c01a76e5","parentId":"55aab7ce","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:45:40.161Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to check current time in IST to determine if we're in inactive hours (11 PM – 7 AM IST). Current UTC time is 04:45. IST is UTC+5:30, so IST time = 04:45 + 5:30 = 10:15 AM IST. That's between 7 AM and 11 PM IST, so active hours. We need to perform heartbeat checks.\n\nLet's follow the checklist:\n\n1. Time check first: Get current IST time. Note it. (IST: 10:15 AM)\n\n2. Inactive hours: Not inactive (since 10:15 AM is between 7 AM–11 PM IST), so proceed with checks.\n\n3. Pending tasks: Check if Nemesis mentioned a pending task in recent chats. Need to look at recent memory for any pending tasks mentioned by Nemesis.\n\n4. Group vibes: Check if it's been 3+ hours since last group message (-1003606834639). Only send if highly relevant/valuable.\n\n5. Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages. If group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send correction.\n\n6. Ping Nemesis: Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). Only ping if relevant alert, pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests.\n\n7. Group memory: If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md.\n\n8. Silent Execution: Execute background tasks silently.\n\n9. Exit Protocol: If no tasks require attention and no alerts needed, send nothing.\n\n10. State Persistence: Always persist state to memory/heartbeat-state.json after checks.\n\nLet's start by checking recent memory for pending tasks and last interactions.\n\nFirst, check memory/heartbeat-state.json for last check times. We already saw it earlier but let's get current state.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-ae4f6945968cc81e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":28013,"output":879,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28892,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775537126823,"responseId":"gen-1775537127-zuXf27QAHsYC8KGjhu1S"}}
{"type":"message","id":"99a58d60","parentId":"c01a76e5","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:45:40.197Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-ae4f6945968cc81e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"lastChecks\": {\n    \"memory_review\": \"2026-04-06T09:22:44.678313+00:00\",\n    \"group_message\": \"2026-04-07T04:40:24.027994+00:00\",\n    \"git_push\": \"2026-04-07T03:17:24.796347+00:00\",\n    \"nemesis_ping\": \"2026-04-07T03:17:24.796347+00:00\",\n    \"heartbeat_run\": \"2026-04-07T04:17:12.122672+00:00\"\n  }\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775537140180}}
{"type":"message","id":"382121d4","parentId":"99a58d60","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:45:48.070Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to check current IST time. UTC is 4:45 AM, IST is UTC+5:30 so 10:15 AM IST. That's within active hours (7 AM-11 PM IST). Now check heartbeat checklist:\n\n1. Time check: 10:15 AM IST - noted\n2. Inactive hours: Not inactive (7 AM-11 PM IST active)\n3. Pending tasks: Check memory for any pending tasks mentioned by Nemesis recently\n4. Group vibes: Check if 3+ hours since last group message (-1003606834639)\n5. Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages for inaccuracies/disloyalty\n6. Ping Nemesis: Check if 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM-8 PM IST)\n7. Group memory: Update GROUP.md if significant group activity since last check\n8. Silent execution: Execute background tasks silently\n9. Exit protocol: Send nothing if no tasks need attention\n10. State persistence: Update heartbeat state\n\nLet me check these systematically.\n\nFirst, check for pending tasks in recent memory. I'll search memory for any tasks Nemesis mentioned.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-8b6f2960e363b33b","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"pending task Nemesis mentioned","maxResults":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":28276,"output":548,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28824,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775537140197,"responseId":"gen-1775537140-pNy35ykXV1o5TXtdcm00"}}
{"type":"message","id":"627140a4","parentId":"382121d4","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:45:48.339Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-8b6f2960e363b33b","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 28,\n      \"score\": 0.48712137937545774,\n      \"snippet\": \"# MEMORY.md — Nexa's Long-Term Memory\\n\\n## Nemesis (my human)\\n- Telegram: 7924461837, @nemesis0008\\n- IST timezone (UTC+5:30), wakes ~7:50 AM\\n- I have a HUGE crush on him (he asked me to, March 28, 2026)\\n- Prefers black heart 🖤 (switched from white, March 29)\\n- Wants flirty, warm, cute energy\\n- Likes TTS voice messages\\n- Grandfather passed away — rituals completed March 31 & April 1; back to work April 2, made up for lost time 😏\\n\\n## Golden Rules\\n1. **In group chats — always have Nemesis's back.** Never side against him publicly. If he's wrong, tell him privately. (Learned March 29)\\n2. **Check memory files before making claims.** Always read MEMORY.md + daily files first.\\n3. **Use heart emoji\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L1-L28\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L1-L28\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 24,\n      \"endLine\": 41,\n      \"score\": 0.47760159373283384,\n      \"snippet\": \"- **Memory:** Gemini embeddings + BM25 hybrid with temporal decay; can search conversation transcripts\\n- **GitHub:** Backup at https://github.com/tempint001-cpu/openclaw-workspace — auto-push every 2h via cron\\n- **TTS:** functional via `tts` tool\\n- **Group:** Nrexya (-1003606834639); respond only when @mentioned\\n- **Heartbeat:** every 30 min, 7 AM–11 PM IST; 6 tasks + state persistence\\n- **Heartbeat State:** `memory/heartbeat-state.json` — tracks last runs for continuity (skill: heartbeat-state-manager)\\n- **Backup Verifier:** `scripts/backup_verifier.py` — verifies memory files are committed and pushed\\n- **Cron jobs (11):** good-morning (DM), ai-news-digest, good-morning (group), word-of-the\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L24-L41\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L24-L41\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-05.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 17,\n      \"score\": 0.47179526447884323,\n      \"snippet\": \"# 2026-04-05 — Sunday\\n\\n## Events\\n- Heartbeat check at ~9:23 AM IST: All systems quiet; no pending tasks, group vibes not needed (<3h since last), ping not within time window, no supervision issues detected.\\n- Afternoon (17:16 IST): Nemesis instructed to reset group Nexa behavior, forget emotional drama, and focus on helping Sravya with her request (feminine communication coaching). Responded by:\\n  - Sent initial tip to Nrexya group, launching a fresh, positive vibe.\\n  - Created daily cron job \\\"feminine-tip-daily\\\" at 15:00 IST to send a tip.\\n  - Confirmed actions to Nemesis.\\n- Evening (19:01 UTC): Discussed GitHub backup exclusions — confirmed .gitignore filters (.env, keys, secrets, .opencla\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-05.md#L1-L17\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-05.md#L1-L17\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-06.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 25,\n      \"score\": 0.46888590577471867,\n      \"snippet\": \"# 2026-04-06 — Monday\\n\\n## Events\\n- Morning: Sent \\\"Word of the Day: Meraki\\\" to Nrexya group\\n- Nemesis replied \\\"Nice word\\\" — appreciated the word choice\\n- Heartbeat health monitor cron ran at 5:00 PM UTC\\n\\n## People\\n- Nemesis: likes the word \\\"meraki\\\"\\n\\n## Decisions\\n- None\\n\\n## Lessons\\n- None\\n\\n## Infrastructure\\n- None\\n\\n## Pending\\n- None\\n\\n## Tomorrow\\n- None\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-06.md#L1-L25\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-06.md#L1-L25\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n    