ing tasks mentioned by Nemesis.\n\nLet me check if there are any mentions in the conversation history.\n\nActually, I can check the session history for any requests from Nemesis.\n\nBut since this is a heartbeat session, the conversation might be limited.\n\nLet me check the session history for this session to see if Nemesis asked for anything.\n\nActually, I just need to make a decision. Based on my checks:\n\n- No pending tasks from Nemesis found\n- Less than 3 hours since last group message (based on heartbeat-state showing group_message task ran recently, though that might be updating GROUP.md)\n- GROUP.md appears accurate and loyal, no corrections needed for group supervision\n- Less than 4 hours since last DM to Nemesis\n- No significant group activity that requires updating GROUP.md (since group_memory task likely ran recently)\n\nTherefore, according to HEARTBEAT.md Exit Protocol: \"If no tasks require attention and no alerts are needed, send absolutely NOTHING. Execute a silent exit.\"\n\nAnd then I need to persist state: update heartbeat state.\n\nI already did that earlier. Let me do it again to be sure.\n\nActually, let me check the current heartbeat state first.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a8df6185cad4ee57","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":40673,"output":4529,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45202,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775537489018,"responseId":"gen-1775537489-UHR18u1dxefHEVV3khvt"}}
