up message, which is less than 3 hours. Therefore, I should NOT send a group message based on the group vibes check.\n\n5. Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\n\nI need to check if I said anything wrong in recent group messages. Since I don't have a direct way to read group messages, I'll rely on the GROUP.md file which should be updated by the group memory task. Looking at GROUP.md, it appears accurate and loyal to Nemesis. I don't see any inaccuracies that I've said recently that need correction.\n\nHowever, to be thorough, let me check if there's a way to get recent group messages. Actually, I already tried to get them earlier but didn't succeed in fetching the actual content. But based on the GROUP.md content and my knowledge of recent actions, I believe I haven't said anything wrong recently.\n\n6. Ping Nemesis: Check if it's been 4+ hours since last DM (between 10 AM–8 PM IST). ONLY ping Nemesis if there is a relevant alert, a pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. Do not send forced casual chatter.\n\nFrom heartbeat-state.json, \"nemesis_ping\": \"2026-04-07T03:17:24.796347+00:00\" which is 03:17 UTC or 8:47 IST.\n\nCurrent time is 11:22 IST, so it's been about 2 hours 35 minutes since last DM, which is less than 4 hours. Therefore, I should NOT ping Nemesis based on time check.\n\nAdditionally, I need to check if there's a relevant alert, pending task reminder, or something highly specific to his interests. From my checks, I don't see any such alerts or pending tasks that need to be communicated to Nemesis.\n\n7. Group memory: If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md.\n\nThe group_message task would handle this, and it was last run at 04:40:24 UTC today. Since we're not sending a group vibes message (less than 3 hours), and I don't see significant group activity requiring an update, this 